# Svelte File Conventions

## Import Organization

Always organize imports in Svelte `<script>` blocks with categorized comment headers in this order:

1. `// SVELTEKIT IMPORTS` — SvelteKit built-ins (`$app/*`, `$env/*`)
2. `// LIBRARIES` — Third-party utilities, actions, helpers
3. `// CLASSES` — Class instances and state management modules
4. `// COMPONENTS` — UI components (shadcn-svelte, custom components)
5. `// LUCIDE ICONS` — Icon imports from `@lucide/svelte`
6. `// ACTIONS` — Server actions and remote functions
7. `// TYPES` — TypeScript types and interfaces

Only include category headers that are actually used. Use **tab** indentation.

Example:
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	// SVELTEKIT IMPORTS
	import { enhance } from '$app/forms';

	// COMPONENTS
	import Button from '@/shared/components/ui/button/button.svelte';

	// LUCIDE ICONS
	import ArrowRightIcon from '@lucide/svelte/icons/arrow-right';
</script>
```

## Style Rules

- Do not use neon or console/terminal aesthetics.
- Prefer modern, premium, clean design language.
- Use scoped `<style>` blocks with `:global()` only when necessary for child component overrides.
- Custom colors should be defined as CSS variables inside the scoped style block.